OL,6,FThe Labour leader instead said he
OL,7,F"simply urged to ensure we have the
OL,8,Fbroadest possible debate".
OL,10,FOn Thursday Leader of the House of
OL,11,FCommons Penny Mordaunt accused Sir
OL,12,FKeir of using the Speaker for
OL,13,Fpolitical gain over the vote, saying
OL,14,F"he puts the interests of the Labour
OL,15,Fparty before the interests of the
OL,16,FBritish people".
OL,18,F"I would never have done to him (the
OL,19,FSpeaker), what the Labour party have
OL,20,Fdone to him", she said, calling Sir
OL,21,FKeir a "weak and fickle leader".
