OL,6,FStephen Flynn, the SNP's Westminster
OL,7,FLeader called for Sir Lindsay Hoyle to
OL,8,Fresign on Thursday, telling him
OL,9,FWednesday's chaos "descended into a
OL,10,Ffarce because of a decision you made".
OL,12,FPrime Minister Rishi Sunak criticised
OL,13,FSir Lindsay's handling of the vote as
OL,14,F"very concerning", but said the
OL,15,FSpeaker is "reflecting on what
OL,16,Fhappened".
OL,18,FSir Lindsay Hoyle apologised for the
OL,19,Fsecond time on Thursday, saying "I
OL,20,Fmade a judgement call... I regret it,
OL,21,FI apologise to the SNP".
